<!---------------------------->
<table cellpadding=2 cellspacing=2>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Recommended Level<br>for starting quest:</b></td><td valign="bottom"> 40<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Starting zone:</b></td><td valign="top"> Eastern Wastes<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Additional zones:</b></td><td valign="top"> -<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Starting NPC:</b></td><td valign="top"> Garadain Glacierbane<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top"><b>Reward:</b></td><td valign="top"> Third Coldain Ring (Gold)<br><br></td></tr>
</table>

This is the third in the series of ten ring quests for progressively better rings.  The components for this can be gathered and combined before completing either of the first two quests.<br>
<br>
After you get the Silver Ring from Garadain, he will ask you to make him a hunting knife to further the Coldain cause.  To make this you need to find a High Quality Walrus Hide, a Wooly Rhino Horn, and a Skinning Rock.<br>
<br>
If you go to the north end of Eastern Wastes along the shore, there are walruses (walri?) and Wooly Rhinos all over the place.  The HQ hides and Horns are not particularly common, but if you're hunting for experience up here, you'll find plenty before you're through.  Take not that the rhinos are pretty rough beasts and will probably require fear kiting if you're soloing at level 40.<br>
<Br>
The skinning rock can be frustrating or simple.  They are ground spawns, but they are NO DROP.  That means you can't tell what it is until you pick it up, then you're stuck with it.  Usually they spawn in the area between the Ry'Gorr fort and the bridge to Iceclad Ocean.  They appear on the ground as little black rocks with red speckles.<br>
<br>
Once you have the three components, take them to a forge and combine them.  The combine is trivial at a smithing skill of 65.  This produces a droppable Coldain Hunting Knife.  If you don't have the smithing skill, and don't want to spend the money to get your skill that high, you can probably find someone else to make the knife for you.  Hand Garadain the knife along with your silver ring.<br>
<br>
Simple as that, you have your Gold Coldain Insignia Ring.<br>
<br>
LORE ITEM MAGIC ITEM NO DROP  <br>
AC: +3 Str: +3 Magic Resist: +3  <br>
Weight: 0.0 <br>
Classes: All Classes  <br>
Races: All Races  <br>
Inventory Slot: Finger <br><br>

